1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,882
- I don't think it will open.
- It's not working.

2
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:11,678
Wake up, Bodyguard and Security!

3
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:23,772
It opened.

4
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:25,108
It's open, Mr. Jang.

5
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:26,776
- Where? That way?
- Yes.

6
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:29,571
I warned you, didn't I?

7
00:00:31,656 --> 00:00:32,490
What on earth?

8
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:43,293
I don't believe this!

9
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:55,345
I don't believe this!

10
00:00:55,346 --> 00:00:56,305
Go that way!

11
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:57,932
That way!

12
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:01,977
- It's this way!
- Come this way, everyone!

13
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:04,063
- Hey! Come this way!
- It's this way!

14
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:06,982
THE AGENTS SPLIT IN TWO DIRECTIONS

15
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:08,693
Hey! Come this way!

16
00:01:19,954 --> 00:01:21,623
Bodyguard, get up.

17
00:01:22,540 --> 00:01:25,000
- We have to go, Security!
- Get over here!

18
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,919
Come on!

19
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,713
- Get over here!
- Come on!

20
00:01:40,391 --> 00:01:42,352
- Which way should we go?
- This way!

21
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:56,241
Lock it!

22
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:12,173
THE MUTANT HORDE KEEPS COMING

23
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:21,098
It was a moment I'll never forget.

24
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:23,183
I don't know if I can say this,

25
00:02:23,184 --> 00:02:25,978
but it was so scary
that I nearly pissed myself.

26
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,729
It was a real shock.

27
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:32,192
<i>Hundreds of them were chasing after us.</i>

28
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:34,903
It's the kind of thing you see in films.

29
00:02:34,904 --> 00:02:37,574
I can't believe I experienced it for real.

30
00:02:44,455 --> 00:02:46,206
I think I might have a heart attack.

31
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:50,419
This means those guards are all dead.

32
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:55,008
CHAIRMAN NA'S ENTOURAGE COULD NOT BE SAVED

33
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:58,594
It looks so tempting to put these on.

34
00:02:58,595 --> 00:02:59,511
What are they?

35
00:02:59,512 --> 00:03:02,264
PROTECTIVE GEAR STORED
IN AN AREA OF THE FACTORY

36
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:04,016
It says, "Put on protective gear."

37
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:05,517
"Safety starts here."

38
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,395
Should we put on the helmets?

39
00:03:09,105 --> 00:03:12,941
I felt more nervous
when I saw the helmets and goggles.

40
00:03:12,942 --> 00:03:15,987
It made me wonder
if something was going to fall on us.

41
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:19,532
- The reading's gone up.
- It has.

42
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:21,491
How many mutants are there?

43
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:23,619
I think there are about 100.

44
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,870
I got caught.

45
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,496
- Did you really?
- Yes.

46
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:28,206
- Did you push them off?
- Yes.

47
00:03:28,207 --> 00:03:29,708
<i>On my way here,</i>

48
00:03:29,709 --> 00:03:31,461
<i>I was chased by 40 mutants.</i>

49
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,378
STAGGERING

50
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:36,214
I was so scared and confused
that my mind went blank.

51
00:03:36,215 --> 00:03:37,591
I couldn't see anything.

52
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:40,345
They just kept growling and slurping.

53
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,183
That was all I could hear.

54
00:03:45,808 --> 00:03:47,351
It really took me by surprise.

55
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:49,728
I've only seen
this kind of thing in films.

56
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:51,605
I can't believe they were
running toward me.

57
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,273
- It's <i>World War Z.</i>
- Exactly.

58
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:56,318
I think it's the first time
I ran while screaming.

59
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,278
I usually just run or scream.

60
00:03:58,279 --> 00:03:59,489
I don't do both.

61
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:00,907
This time, I did both.

62
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,409
RUNNING WHILE SHOUTING

63
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:06,495
It's the first time I ran while screaming.

64
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:07,830
That was so scary.

65
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:10,832
Let's look for clues.

66
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,335
I saw a door over there.

67
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:15,921
CLICK

68
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:17,006
Is it opening?

69
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:18,758
No, it's not.

70
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:21,594
I think it's this door.

71
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:25,681
What is this?

72
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:27,100
It's locked from the inside.

73
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:29,017
It won't open, John.

74
00:04:29,018 --> 00:04:30,519
ALL DOORS ARE LOCKED

75
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,020
It's not opening?

76
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:35,984
WHERE DO WE GO?

77
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:38,903
There's no key, right?

78
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:48,162
Look at this.

79
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:51,164
Look at this.

80
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:52,458
Check this out.

81
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:55,585
Over here.

82
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:56,503
Unbelievable.

83
00:04:56,504 --> 00:04:57,421
Let's go.

84
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:58,423
BEHIND THE SHEET IS…

85
00:04:59,007 --> 00:04:59,923
What is this?

86
00:04:59,924 --> 00:05:00,758
A SECRET PASSAGE

87
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,178
I think we need to walk through this.

88
00:05:05,179 --> 00:05:07,180
A NARROW PASSAGE LEADING TO THE OTHER SIDE

89
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:08,474
Oh, man.

90
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:10,976
- But…
- Yes?

91
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:12,602
I took this down, and look what I found.

92
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:13,562
- Oh, gosh.
- No way.

93
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:15,523
Right? I saw it as soon as I got here.

94
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:17,566
- Was this always here?
- Yes.

95
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:19,318
It's been here since we entered.

96
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,320
There's nothing inside.

97
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,156
They must have crawled through this.

98
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:24,656
I've got chills.

99
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:26,116
- Did it crawl this way?
- Isn't it out?

100
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,034
I'm scared.

101
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:29,494
There are more of them than I expected.

102
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:31,747
- There are almost 100.
- You're right.

103
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:34,124
I think we made a mistake earlier

104
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:37,336
- by splitting up in different directions.
- You're right.

105
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:39,046
- It's this way!
- Come this way, everyone!

106
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,797
- Hey, over here!
- It's this way!

107
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:42,591
- You're right.
- We need to decide where to go.

108
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,301
Yeah, we were too unprepared.

109
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:47,763
Guard Jang pointed in a vague direction.

110
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:50,390
You should have stopped
asking about his name.

111
00:05:50,391 --> 00:05:52,059
- Why didn't you believe him?
- It's your fault.

112
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,477
- You should have opened the door.
- Wait.

113
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:54,770
Before we came out…

114
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:57,606
- He's a mutant now.
- We agreed not to trust anyone.

115
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,149
So, that's why I questioned him.

116
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,068
What if they betrayed him
and then collapsed?

117
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:03,236
Remember how, when we were
first given this assignment…

118
00:06:03,237 --> 00:06:04,696
Please untie our hands.

119
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:06,865
What if he's a traitor?

120
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,408
- Are we sure about this?
- No.

121
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:10,118
What's your name, Head of Security?

122
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:11,996
I'm Guard Jang.

123
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:15,875
GUARD JANG AND HIS CREW DIED AS SUSPECTS

124
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:19,462
- Let's go ahead. But from now on…
- What's that?

125
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:24,133
A noise is coming from inside.

126
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,597
Don't you hear a lot of noise from there?

127
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:32,766
Please…

128
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,184
Wait.

129
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:35,520
- I'm scared.
- Wait.

130
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:39,899
- You brought it.
- Yes, I did.

131
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,526
- Right now…
- Where are we?

132
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:44,194
- We left the office building.
- Yes.

133
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:45,320
This is the factory building.

134
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:47,364
- We came this way.
- Okay.

135
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:48,491
- We came through here.
- I see.

136
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:51,785
- If we go in through there…
- Yes?

137
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,662
- It's where the chairman is.
- Right.

138
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:55,580
- But it's not opening right now.
- No, it's not.

139
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:58,208
- So, we need to go around.
- We go inside.

140
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,543
- And then, turn left?
- Yes.

141
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:01,002
We have to go left.

142
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:03,547
- But since we can hear noises…
- Yes, we need to be careful.

143
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:05,507
We don't know what's waiting for us.

144
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:07,759
- The factory is really large.
- It is.

145
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,137
I miss my mom.

146
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:11,847
All right. Let's go in.

147
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:12,931
THE OLDEST LEADS BY EXAMPLE

148
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:13,766
You first, Yong-jin?

149
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:16,226
CLOSE CALL

150
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,394
That fool.

151
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:18,938
Geez, Yong-jin.

152
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,565
- Pull yourself together.
- I'm sorry.

153
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:24,276
It's not the time for slapstick comedy.

154
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:25,820
Fasten your helmets.

155
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:28,238
YONG-JIN ENTERS
WITH HIS HELMET IN HIS HAND

156
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:29,573
But if we all go inside…

157
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:31,409
Be quiet.

158
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:35,246
I'm scared.

159
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:43,379
GOING IN ONE BY ONE

160
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:52,680
What is it?

161
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:55,015
- It's too big.
- What?

162
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:56,142
It's massive.

163
00:07:58,019 --> 00:07:59,061
OVERWHELMED

164
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:03,232
This is crazy.

165
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:33,513
AGENTS OF MYSTERY SEASON 2

166
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:36,891
This is crazy. What do we do?

167
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:43,188
Be quiet.

168
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:44,314
They're here.

169
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:45,900
- The mutants are here.
- They're here?

170
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:48,361
- Where?
- Over there.

171
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:54,200
FACTORY 2

172
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:02,832
It's the mutants from earlier.

173
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,585
They're all over there.

174
00:09:13,844 --> 00:09:16,013
THEY'RE OVER THERE

175
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:18,558
BE QUIET, CROUCH DOWN

176
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,560
CAN YOU SEE THEM?

177
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:25,855
WHIMPER

178
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:27,691
WE HAVE TO GO THAT WAY

179
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:29,150
Oh, my gosh.

180
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:30,778
There are too many of them.

181
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,910
LET'S FIRST LOOK FOR A PLACE TO HIDE

182
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:40,912
There are so many of them.

183
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:42,623
There are way too many.

184
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,795
We need to go around.

185
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:50,047
I'm too scared.

186
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:54,634
I'm really sensitive to noises.

187
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:56,678
And they kept growling like this.

188
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,471
Every so often, they got really loud.

189
00:09:58,472 --> 00:10:01,684
EXPERT MUTANT GROWLER

190
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:04,770
We had no choice but to walk past them.

191
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:11,986
It says to follow the blue arrows.

192
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:13,403
BEWARE OF FALLING OBJECTS

193
00:10:13,404 --> 00:10:15,113
FOLLOW THE BLUE ARROWS

194
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:16,365
BLUE ARROWS?

195
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:18,575
LOOKING AROUND

196
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:21,328
THE AGENTS' CURRENT LOCATION

197
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:24,831
We had to follow the blue arrows
down the closest path.

198
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:25,708
THROUGH THE TUNNEL

199
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:30,712
A BLUE ARROW ON THE LEFT WALL

200
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:34,424
I could see on the map
that if we kept going forward,

201
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:37,177
<i>we would get to Factory 3
where the chairman was.</i>

202
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:39,846
- Isn't it over there?
- Yes, that way.

203
00:10:39,847 --> 00:10:41,349
FACTORY 3

204
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,102
There are more here.

205
00:10:46,103 --> 00:10:47,355
- They're here too?
- There are more.

206
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:49,732
There are more here?

207
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:56,155
Hold on.

208
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:59,283
MORE MUTANTS BEHIND THE WALL

209
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:04,120
We can't go that way.

210
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:06,206
- Isn't it this way?
- We can't go.

211
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:08,041
We need to go around.

212
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,669
Everybody, gather around.

213
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:12,796
Our goal is to get into that room.

214
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:14,839
- But this way is blocked.
- Right.

215
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,966
We need to go around.

216
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:17,968
Okay.

217
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:20,095
I'll have nightmares about this.

218
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:22,514
There are arrows in that direction.

219
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,517
I think we just need to stay out of sight.

220
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,644
I think it's like a maze.

221
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:28,479
Like a maze?

222
00:11:29,522 --> 00:11:33,526
TAKING THE OPPOSITE ROUTE

223
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:35,403
FLINCH

224
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:39,657
We need to crouch down.

225
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:42,159
Get as low as you can.

226
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:48,624
HIDE AND TAKE COVER

227
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,419
Why are they acting
like moths flew in their mouths?

228
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,714
STAIRWAY

229
00:11:56,715 --> 00:11:57,758
How do we get there?

230
00:11:58,384 --> 00:11:59,884
This is crazy.

231
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:00,886
There they are.

232
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:06,891
TAKING THE STAIRS

233
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:10,895
DISCOVERS A SIDE PATH

234
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:13,565
STAIRS OR SIDE PATH?

235
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:16,819
DO-HOON FOLLOWS YONG-JIN

236
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,951
When we got up the stairs,

237
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:27,036
we could see everything a bit better.

238
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:31,834
<i>We saw the mutants gathered at the center.</i>

239
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,590
Following the blue arrows seems right.

240
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:39,716
Let's follow the arrows.

241
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,886
SECOND BLUE ARROW FOUND

242
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:44,472
OKAY

243
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:48,434
The mutants are gathered over there.

244
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:50,895
We need to go around.

245
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:52,770
PEEKING OUT

246
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:54,315
We need to head that way.

247
00:12:54,815 --> 00:12:55,941
There's a passage at the end.

248
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:01,363
COME OVER HERE

249
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:03,782
THIRD BLUE ARROW FOUND

250
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:11,040
We need to go behind the box
and then move to the barrels.

251
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:12,917
Watch your step.

252
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:19,590
Wait a minute.

253
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:23,009
If we get caught here,

254
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:24,344
we have to run, okay?

255
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,637
Where do we run to?

256
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:27,388
- Follow the arrow.
- Make sure to run.

257
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,306
We'll lead the way.

258
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:29,849
It's only if we get caught.

259
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,727
- Let's move slowly for now.
- Okay.

260
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:36,606
YONG-JIN GOES FIRST

261
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:37,815
DO-HOON GOES NEXT

262
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:39,484
TIP-TOEING QUIETLY

263
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:40,652
DASHING

264
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,988
THUD

265
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:50,079
THE MUTANTS REACT VIOLENTLY

266
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:53,165
SILENT MODE BACK ON

267
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:55,584
I'm scared.

268
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,711
MONITORING THE SITUATION

269
00:13:58,712 --> 00:13:59,922
Should we go now?

270
00:14:01,298 --> 00:14:03,926
YONG-JIN MOVES ACROSS

271
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:06,220
COME OVER

272
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,055
NODS

273
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:11,517
JOHN PARK MOVES ACROSS

274
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:14,811
MORE THUDDING

275
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:17,939
THE MUTANTS GET EVEN MORE AGITATED

276
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,233
Look at this.

277
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,776
THROWS A PIECE OF WOOD

278
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:22,611
BANG

279
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:27,240
MOVES WHILE THE MUTANTS ARE DISTRACTED

280
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:28,742
THIS IS IT!

281
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:34,664
EVERYBODY FOLLOWS, ONE AT A TIME

282
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:38,794
I noticed that the mutants
reacted very sensitively to sounds.

283
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:40,962
THE LOUD NOISE EARLIER
THUD

284
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:43,424
MADE THE MUTANTS ESPECIALLY AGITATED

285
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:46,176
YONG-JIN WATCHES CLOSELY

286
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,971
HE GRABS A PIECE OF WOOD

287
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:50,514
THROWS IN MORE BAIT

288
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:52,765
THEY MOVE WHILE THE MUTANTS ARE DISTRACTED

289
00:14:52,766 --> 00:14:53,934
Go first, Gabee.

290
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:56,102
Come over one by one.

291
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:57,229
Come now.

292
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:00,732
THROWS ANOTHER OBJECT

293
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:01,983
BANG

294
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:03,694
THE MUTANTS REACT FIERCELY

295
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:05,403
Let's move.

296
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:06,238
Let's go.

297
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,867
USING NOISE AS A DISTRACTION

298
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:12,327
THEY SAFELY CROSS THE PASSAGE

299
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:13,495
We did it.

300
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,749
We can't let our guard down.

301
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,752
Stay alert. Go on ahead.

302
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:24,048
GOING UP ANOTHER SET OF STAIRS

303
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,096
FOURTH BLUE ARROW FOUND

304
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,140
We're nearly there.

305
00:15:37,394 --> 00:15:38,895
ONE MORE ARROW

306
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:39,938
FIFTH BLUE ARROW FOUND

307
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:41,606
- We should go that way.
- Is there an arrow?

308
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,107
It's by that wall.

309
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,901
IT'S OVER THERE

310
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:47,654
FOLLOW THE BLUE ARROWS ON THE FLOOR

311
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:51,407
THE FIRST BLUE ARROW

312
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:54,118
IS POINTING TO THE FINAL EXIT

313
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:55,328
It's by the wall.

314
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:57,790
CLOSE TO THE FINAL DESTINATION

315
00:15:58,290 --> 00:15:59,583
Do we need to run?

316
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,335
I'LL GO FIRST

317
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,338
FAILED

318
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:06,966
They're right in front of us.

319
00:16:09,551 --> 00:16:11,803
A SWARM OF MUTANTS

320
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,055
Is there anything we can throw?

321
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:14,806
You need something to throw?

322
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:15,723
What about this?

323
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:16,641
SELFLESS SACRIFICE

324
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:17,684
REJECTED

325
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:19,185
I think it will be okay.

326
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:20,103
Don't you think so?

327
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:21,980
They're right in front of us.

328
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,481
The room was right in front of us.

329
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:25,316
<i>We were so close.</i>

330
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:27,319
<i>I thought we could make it if we ran.</i>

331
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:33,449
MOVES COVERTLY

332
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:35,159
Nobody was moving.

333
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,078
So I thought someone had to step up,

334
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:39,123
and I should be the one to do it.

335
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,083
DETERMINED

336
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,377
SLYLY

337
00:16:49,466 --> 00:16:52,468
MISSION SUCCESSFUL

338
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:54,679
INSPIRED BY HYE-RI'S COURAGE

339
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,557
YONG-JIN MOVES

340
00:16:57,391 --> 00:16:59,350
GABEE MOVES

341
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:00,685
SUCCESS

342
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:01,602
DO-HOON MOVES

343
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:02,813
BEEPING

344
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:08,944
Let's go. Run!

345
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:13,032
Run!

346
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:19,037
- Keep running!
- Damn it.

347
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:19,872
KEEP RUNNING

348
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:23,834
Run!

349
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:25,793
Hey!

350
00:17:25,794 --> 00:17:27,504
Keep going. Run!

351
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,801
KARINA'S FALLEN OVER

352
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:35,553
Hurry! Run!

353
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:37,056
Wait! Where are the others?

354
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:41,393
JOHN QUICKLY REACHES OUT

355
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:46,898
- Run!
- Get in here!

356
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,441
- Hurry!
- Get in!

357
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:49,525
Run!

358
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:50,443
Get in!

359
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:51,487
Come on.

360
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:58,660
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm okay.

361
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,538
DOOR SHUTS JUST IN TIME

362
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:07,085
Are you okay? Did they get you?

363
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:08,920
- I'm fine. I fell over.
- You fell over?

364
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:10,755
I lost my balance because of the bag.

365
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:12,216
- You fell over?
- I'm okay.

366
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:16,719
I WAS NOT OKAY

367
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:19,055
I wasn't hurt, but I was so embarrassed.

368
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:21,516
It was so embarrassing.

369
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,601
I had the bag on my shoulders.

370
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:26,229
<i>I was running so quickly</i>

371
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,939
<i>that the bag bounced and hit my head.</i>

372
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:29,440
I thought I was a goner.

373
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:30,942
<i>But John was next to me.</i>

374
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:32,485
<i>He helped me get up and run inside.</i>

375
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:34,070
<i>So I barely made it.</i>

376
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:36,030
He's my savior.

377
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:37,990
I owe him big time.

378
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:39,700
I didn't know until we got inside.

379
00:18:39,701 --> 00:18:42,662
<i>Someone said Karina had fallen over.</i>

380
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:44,456
I felt really bad.

381
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,667
GABEE IN THAT MOMENT…

382
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:49,001
Damn it. We're screwed.

383
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:50,045
Run for it!

384
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:53,381
I felt bad for not taking care of her.

385
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:54,842
I'm fine.

386
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:59,178
- I heard a noise over there.
- What now?

387
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:01,055
- There's a person.
- Where?

388
00:19:01,056 --> 00:19:03,099
- There's a person over there.
- There is.

389
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,143
Wait a minute.

390
00:19:08,021 --> 00:19:09,772
THERE'S A DOORWAY

391
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:10,691
Damn it.

392
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:13,902
IT'S CLOSED WITH A LATCH

393
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:20,075
Does it open?

394
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:22,827
THE DOOR JOHN OPENED IS…

395
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,328
It won't open, John.

396
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:25,413
It's not opening?

397
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:27,916
THE DOOR THAT DIDN'T OPEN FROM THE OUTSIDE

398
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:30,293
This is it.

399
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:31,210
It's good for a getaway.

400
00:19:31,211 --> 00:19:33,255
- I'll leave it open just in case.
- Yes, leave it open.

401
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:36,091
But can't they come in?

402
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:37,885
Should we close it?

403
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:42,514
GETAWAY SECURED FOR NOW

404
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:48,477
GOING BACK TOWARD THE NOISE

405
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:50,647
This place is…

406
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:52,899
I see people.

407
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,318
There are people over there.

408
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:57,863
What is that?

409
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:04,368
What is that?

410
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:05,621
What is all this?

411
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:28,851
Unlike the mutant cocoons
we'd seen before,

412
00:20:28,852 --> 00:20:30,478
they were something else entirely.

413
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:33,190
<i>There were just so many.</i>

414
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:38,069
<i>When we walked inside,</i>

415
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:41,113
<i>we saw something that glowed green.</i>

416
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:41,949
<i>Maybe it was a host?</i>

417
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:46,953
<i>There were cocoon husks
and people collapsed on the floor.</i>

418
00:20:46,954 --> 00:20:48,372
<i>It was all very eerie.</i>

419
00:20:49,706 --> 00:20:51,208
Look at all these people.

420
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:57,964
It's moving.

421
00:20:57,965 --> 00:20:59,716
- What?
- That thing's moving.

422
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:05,721
I think these people are alive.

423
00:21:05,722 --> 00:21:06,974
This is so gross.

424
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:14,313
- I think they're becoming zombies.
- Yes.

425
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:16,565
- We need to hurry.
- We don't have much time.

426
00:21:16,566 --> 00:21:17,818
- We need to solve this.
- Right.

427
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:19,695
- Be careful.
- Okay.

428
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:24,908
What are all these tools?

429
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:26,617
This is where they were tortured.

430
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:27,828
There are mutant cocoons here too.

431
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:32,624
CRUEL TORTURE DEVICES

432
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:37,128
MUTANT COCOON REMAINS

433
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:39,797
I think this is
where Chairman Na was tortured.

434
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:41,757
- I think they're threatening him.
- With torture?

435
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:45,429
- I bet they'll pull out his teeth.
- Oh, no!

436
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,265
- This is where they did it.
- Yes.

437
00:21:48,765 --> 00:21:50,224
AN ABANDONED BLACK SECURITY CASE
ON THE FLOOR

438
00:21:50,225 --> 00:21:52,728
It's what we saw earlier.

439
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:58,190
- Okay.
- Shouldn't we open it?

440
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,692
Let's do rock, paper, scissors.

441
00:21:59,693 --> 00:22:00,609
CHUCKLING

442
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:02,695
- Who wants to do it?
- I didn't expect that from you.

443
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:04,071
- Who'll do it?
- Rock, paper, scissors?

444
00:22:04,072 --> 00:22:05,656
Let's do rock, paper, scissors.

445
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:06,533
Let's do it.

446
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,159
But first…

447
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,995
IMPATIENT HYE-RI OPENS THE CASE

448
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:17,919
THE INNER COMPARTMENT IS SEALED

449
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:20,379
This green liquid…

450
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:21,506
Do we need to open it?

451
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,050
- I guess we do.
- We need the chairman.

452
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:25,677
Only Chairman Na can open this.

453
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:28,346
- He said Chairman Na had it.
- The chip.

454
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:29,764
Additionally,

455
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:33,684
it can only be accessed
with a chip implanted in Chairman Na.

456
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:37,105
He said it was implanted in his body.

457
00:22:42,652 --> 00:22:44,362
Let's look at the photo.

458
00:22:49,659 --> 00:22:51,452
WHAT IS THAT?

459
00:22:51,453 --> 00:22:52,287
FLASHLIGHT ON

460
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:57,500
Is it this person?

461
00:22:57,501 --> 00:22:58,918
Is there someone here?

462
00:22:58,919 --> 00:23:00,504
Yes, there is.

463
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:04,341
THERE IS A FACE INSIDE THE MUTANT COCOON

464
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:06,218
Is it Chairman Na?

465
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:09,178
- I think so.
- Can I see the photo?

466
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:11,223
We can see better from here.

467
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:15,477
- I think it's him.
- It is him.

468
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:18,687
Chairman Na was the key.

469
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:22,191
Part of our mission
was to save Chairman Na.

470
00:23:22,192 --> 00:23:23,609
But he was already a mutant.

471
00:23:23,610 --> 00:23:26,195
So, we weren't sure if we could save him.

472
00:23:26,196 --> 00:23:29,616
Yong-jin, I don't think he's dead.

473
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:31,826
He's still alive and breathing.

474
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:33,202
He could possibly wake up.

475
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:34,578
HOW ABOUT THIS?

476
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:36,413
- It's to rip open.
- Oh, I see.

477
00:23:36,414 --> 00:23:38,916
WE THOUGHT IT WAS A WEAPON

478
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:40,626
- He said it was implanted in his body.
- Yes.

479
00:23:40,627 --> 00:23:42,128
We have to rip it open.

480
00:23:42,129 --> 00:23:43,338
MUST RIP THE MUTANT COCOON TO GET THE CHIP

481
00:23:46,883 --> 00:23:47,801
GROSSED OUT

482
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:49,635
- Should I do it?
- Go on, Karina.

483
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:50,886
Go, Karina, the female warrior.

484
00:23:50,887 --> 00:23:52,263
Should I?

485
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:53,472
I'm going in.

486
00:23:53,473 --> 00:23:55,099
Do it. Cut it in half.

487
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,601
Please don't leap out.

488
00:24:04,985 --> 00:24:06,485
I'm sweating bullets.

489
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:08,071
Be careful.

490
00:24:11,908 --> 00:24:14,452
SLOWLY SEEING MORE OF CHAIRMAN NA

491
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:18,205
RETCHING

492
00:24:18,206 --> 00:24:19,748
She's squeamish.

493
00:24:19,749 --> 00:24:21,125
Karina's brave but squeamish.

494
00:24:21,126 --> 00:24:22,209
Aren't there any scissors?

495
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:24,461
I think we need scissors.

496
00:24:24,462 --> 00:24:26,046
I saw pliers.

497
00:24:26,047 --> 00:24:28,465
JOHN FINDS THE GIANT SCISSORS

498
00:24:28,466 --> 00:24:29,301
Here it is.

499
00:24:31,219 --> 00:24:34,388
KARINA PICKS UP A GRUB AX
THAT LOOKS LIKE PLIERS

500
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:35,389
A GRUB AX IN HER LEFT HAND

501
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,432
Look at her.

502
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:37,475
A METAL PIPE IN HER RIGHT HAND

503
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:45,149
STARTS CUTTING WITH THE GIANT SCISSORS

504
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,109
Is it working?

505
00:24:55,285 --> 00:24:56,328
Wait.

506
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:59,998
Should we check around his hand?

507
00:25:00,582 --> 00:25:04,960
- Most implants are put into the wrist.
- That's true.

508
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,796
- Let's try.
- Let's put his hand on the case.

509
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:12,802
CONTACT

510
00:25:14,638 --> 00:25:16,305
THE SECURITY CASE DOESN'T REACT

511
00:25:16,306 --> 00:25:17,474
Is there another way?

512
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:20,268
Inside his body…

513
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:22,394
That means…

514
00:25:22,395 --> 00:25:24,355
I'll do a quick search.

515
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:25,482
Yes, search him.

516
00:25:26,316 --> 00:25:28,192
It must be somewhere in his body.

517
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:29,485
Maybe it's in his nose.

518
00:25:29,486 --> 00:25:31,112
EXCUSE US

519
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:35,407
I don't feel anything.

520
00:25:35,408 --> 00:25:37,452
What would we have to use to open it?

521
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:42,207
Where do we insert the chip?

522
00:25:43,416 --> 00:25:45,794
There's no key or anything.

523
00:25:50,173 --> 00:25:51,341
Oh, I see.

524
00:25:53,301 --> 00:25:55,469
There's a USB port here.

525
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:56,888
It's like a key.

526
00:25:57,931 --> 00:26:00,976
THERE IS A SMALL SLOT INSIDE THE CASE

527
00:26:01,559 --> 00:26:04,229
HIDDEN PORT FOR INSERTING THE CHIP

528
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:05,855
This is the key.

529
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:09,401
Could it be in his chest?

530
00:26:09,943 --> 00:26:11,111
Check just above his stomach.

531
00:26:11,736 --> 00:26:13,028
You mean like Iron Man?

532
00:26:13,029 --> 00:26:14,489
Yes, exactly.

533
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:17,324
No, it's not there.

534
00:26:17,325 --> 00:26:19,118
- If it's in his body…
- That's what he said.

535
00:26:19,119 --> 00:26:20,911
…could it be behind his ear?

536
00:26:20,912 --> 00:26:23,289
Can you check behind his ears?

537
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:24,331
Can you feel anything?

538
00:26:24,332 --> 00:26:27,919
CHECKING BEHIND HIS EAR

539
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:30,671
- Hey.
- Did you find it?

540
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:31,839
Is it behind his ear?

541
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,590
I thought it would be.

542
00:26:33,591 --> 00:26:35,884
<i>It was behind his right ear.</i>

543
00:26:35,885 --> 00:26:38,679
There was a small tear in the skin

544
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,472
that I missed the first time.

545
00:26:40,473 --> 00:26:44,311
I put my fingers inside it,
and I felt something.

546
00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:47,021
We found it.

547
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:48,022
Oh, gosh.

548
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:49,940
- Can you get it out, Yong-jin?
- Hang on.

549
00:26:49,941 --> 00:26:50,899
How did you know, Gabee?

550
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:52,568
That's where they put it in <i>Squid Game.</i>

551
00:26:52,569 --> 00:26:54,612
That's right. They put it behind the ear.

552
00:26:55,322 --> 00:26:57,157
It's in too deep.

553
00:26:58,116 --> 00:26:59,867
Yong-jin's operating on him.

554
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:02,286
AFTER A QUICK OPERATION

555
00:27:02,287 --> 00:27:05,497
THE CHIP IS RETRIEVED

556
00:27:05,498 --> 00:27:07,042
- We did it.
- We got it out.

557
00:27:07,542 --> 00:27:09,585
In fishing terms,

558
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:13,005
<i>it was like catching
a six-foot monster fish.</i>

559
00:27:13,006 --> 00:27:15,466
There's something rewarding
about using your hands.

560
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:17,926
It was a great feeling.

561
00:27:17,927 --> 00:27:19,804
I'm still enjoying the high.

562
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:22,390
Wait, we need to get out--

563
00:27:25,518 --> 00:27:26,686
Put it in.

564
00:27:50,418 --> 00:27:51,668
Where do we go?

565
00:27:51,669 --> 00:27:53,170
- Let's go.
- Let's take it with us.

566
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:54,213
Let's go.

567
00:27:54,214 --> 00:27:55,130
We have to get away.

568
00:27:55,131 --> 00:27:57,216
- No, it's okay. We can stay here.
- Shut the door.

569
00:27:57,217 --> 00:27:58,343
Close the door.

570
00:27:58,843 --> 00:28:00,387
- We can do it here.
- Here?

571
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:29,207
We need the flashlight.

572
00:28:31,292 --> 00:28:32,127
Here you go.

573
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:36,547
It's open.

574
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:37,881
- Let's see what this is.
- What is it?

575
00:28:37,882 --> 00:28:39,383
- It's a needle.
- A needle.

576
00:28:39,384 --> 00:28:41,760
<i>When we opened the briefcase,</i>

577
00:28:41,761 --> 00:28:44,680
<i>we saw two needles and some liquids.</i>

578
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:46,682
<i>There was also an electronic manual.</i>

579
00:28:46,683 --> 00:28:48,475
- How do we use the needles?
- What is this?

580
00:28:48,476 --> 00:28:49,560
Could it be a vaccine?

581
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:50,769
Is it a vaccine?

582
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:52,104
- Hang on.
- What is it?

583
00:28:52,105 --> 00:28:54,356
Why are there two colors?
It's making me nervous.

584
00:28:54,357 --> 00:28:56,359
I think we need to choose, right?

585
00:28:56,943 --> 00:28:58,278
What about this one, John?

586
00:29:00,155 --> 00:29:01,113
I know what this is.

587
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:02,698
This is…

588
00:29:02,699 --> 00:29:03,615
Is it an e-book?

589
00:29:03,616 --> 00:29:04,533
I think it's an e-book.

590
00:29:04,534 --> 00:29:05,576
It's an electronic book.

591
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:07,203
- You mean an e-book?
- Yes.

592
00:29:08,246 --> 00:29:10,206
I said that about three times.

593
00:29:11,458 --> 00:29:13,960
E-BOOK SWITCHED ON

594
00:29:14,711 --> 00:29:16,379
- Can you read it for us?
- Okay.

595
00:29:20,008 --> 00:29:23,427
<i>"In December 2024,
on the coastline of Florida,</i>

596
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:27,056
<i>a UFO plummeted to the ground."</i>

597
00:29:27,807 --> 00:29:29,266
It's linked to what we did before.

598
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:30,684
Yes, it's our last mission.

599
00:29:30,685 --> 00:29:32,019
<i>Six months ago,</i>

600
00:29:32,020 --> 00:29:36,690
<i>a 43-meter-wide object plummeted
onto the coastline of southern Florida.</i>

601
00:29:36,691 --> 00:29:39,067
<i>"A mysterious life form of alien origin</i>

602
00:29:39,068 --> 00:29:42,404
<i>was found inside the object."</i>

603
00:29:42,405 --> 00:29:45,783
<i>"This life form was named F-1."</i>

604
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:48,911
<i>"Analysis confirmed
it was a complex life form</i>

605
00:29:48,912 --> 00:29:50,579
<i>that does not exist on earth."</i>

606
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:53,707
<i>"It responds autonomously and shape-shifts
in a way that can't be explained</i>

607
00:29:53,708 --> 00:29:57,504
<i>by currently existing
biological classification systems."</i>

608
00:30:00,131 --> 00:30:03,133
<i>"Red protrusions connected
to blood vessels were discovered."</i>

609
00:30:03,134 --> 00:30:06,970
<i>"This part seems
especially sensitive to outside stimuli,</i>

610
00:30:06,971 --> 00:30:08,972
<i>and has been designated as the Core."</i>

611
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:09,890
RED PROTRUSIONS… THE CORE?

612
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:14,479
A cluster of red protrusions
that are connected to vessels…

613
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:17,147
F-1 also emits a gas.

614
00:30:17,148 --> 00:30:20,026
- That must be the black gas.
- It must be.

615
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:22,820
This is from the video we saw last time.

616
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:25,572
LIVING ORGANISMS THAT BREATHE IN BLACK GAS

617
00:30:25,573 --> 00:30:29,576
THROW UP A VISCOUS FILAMENT
THAT BECOMES A MUTANT COCOON

618
00:30:29,577 --> 00:30:33,540
AND TRANSFORM INTO MUTANTS

619
00:30:34,999 --> 00:30:36,166
There's more.

620
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:37,918
<i>On the next page,</i>

621
00:30:37,919 --> 00:30:41,797
there were explanations
of all the life forms we'd seen.

622
00:30:41,798 --> 00:30:44,466
"They are extremely sensitive
to smells and sounds."

623
00:30:44,467 --> 00:30:46,802
It says they have poor sight.

624
00:30:46,803 --> 00:30:49,054
- You're right.
- They're blind?

625
00:30:49,055 --> 00:30:50,931
That's why they couldn't see us.

626
00:30:50,932 --> 00:30:54,393
They didn't seem to see us
when we were quietly getting away.

627
00:30:54,394 --> 00:30:56,562
We realized they had really poor vision.

628
00:30:56,563 --> 00:31:02,276
THE MUTANTS DID NOT SEE THEM MOVE
DUE TO THEIR POOR VISION

629
00:31:02,277 --> 00:31:03,443
ON THE OTHER HAND

630
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:06,613
THEY REACTED SENSITIVELY TO LOUD NOISES

631
00:31:06,614 --> 00:31:08,115
"Behavioral Traits."

632
00:31:08,116 --> 00:31:11,785
<i>"The mutants seem to be protecting F-1."</i>

633
00:31:11,786 --> 00:31:15,289
<i>"When they sense the presence
of a different species like us,</i>

634
00:31:15,290 --> 00:31:18,208
<i>they show indiscriminate aggression."</i>

635
00:31:18,209 --> 00:31:19,252
It's so scary.

636
00:31:19,752 --> 00:31:24,006
"But if a life form is covered in goo
from a mutant cocoon,

637
00:31:24,007 --> 00:31:26,592
the mutants temporarily mistake it
as one of their own and do not attack."

638
00:31:26,593 --> 00:31:28,051
We need to cover ourselves

639
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:29,679
- in the goo of a mutant cocoon.
- Yes.

640
00:31:30,346 --> 00:31:32,890
I think we'll be safe if we're covered.

641
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:35,100
- That's how we get there.
- Yes.

642
00:31:35,101 --> 00:31:37,603
- The effect is temporary.
- We need to move quickly.

643
00:31:37,604 --> 00:31:38,646
We must be quick.

644
00:31:40,273 --> 00:31:42,525
I think we'll be okay
as long as we're quiet.

645
00:31:44,027 --> 00:31:46,695
"Emergency Procedures Manual."

646
00:31:46,696 --> 00:31:49,156
<i>What does it say about using the needles?</i>

647
00:31:49,157 --> 00:31:50,908
<i>"The needles must be injected</i>

648
00:31:50,909 --> 00:31:54,661
<i>into the two Cores
that are connected to blood vessels."</i>

649
00:31:54,662 --> 00:31:57,372
There are two Cores.

650
00:31:57,373 --> 00:31:59,082
<i>"If the high-energy fusion is successful,</i>

651
00:31:59,083 --> 00:32:01,209
<i>there will be a visible color change,</i>

652
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:03,086
<i>and it will explode in ten seconds."</i>

653
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:05,130
It takes ten seconds for it to explode.

654
00:32:05,131 --> 00:32:07,966
We'll have to get away before it explodes.

655
00:32:07,967 --> 00:32:09,176
All right, then.

656
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:10,844
Let's first prepare the needles.

657
00:32:10,845 --> 00:32:13,221
Let's use one of each color.

658
00:32:13,222 --> 00:32:15,557
I don't know how to use this.

659
00:32:15,558 --> 00:32:16,976
We just draw back the syringe.

660
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:19,686
We need to use one red

661
00:32:19,687 --> 00:32:22,105
- and one blue, right?
- That's right.

662
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:24,149
Yes, since there are two Cores.

663
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:26,527
MUST INJECT THE NEEDLE INTO TWO CORES!

664
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:29,697
Match the colors.

665
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:32,741
We should fill it all the way.

666
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:34,661
- Yes, let's fill it up.
- Put in as much as we can.

667
00:32:38,998 --> 00:32:41,417
Okay, that's good.

668
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:44,962
NEEDLES PREPARED

669
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:47,548
DO-HOON APPROACHES THE MUTANT COCOON

670
00:32:48,925 --> 00:32:52,427
We had to cover ourselves
with the mutant cocoon's substance.

671
00:32:52,428 --> 00:32:56,056
That would make the mutants
see us as one of them.

672
00:32:56,057 --> 00:32:57,767
So, of course, we had to do it.

673
00:33:01,688 --> 00:33:06,191
It was slippery, sticky, and very thick.

674
00:33:06,192 --> 00:33:07,694
Let's put on as much as we can.

675
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:09,820
As much as we can.

676
00:33:09,821 --> 00:33:11,989
RETCHING

677
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:14,742
A NAUSEATING DISGUISE

678
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:17,704
GETTING SOAKED

679
00:33:18,413 --> 00:33:20,747
- Is this enough?
- I think you need more. Come here.

680
00:33:20,748 --> 00:33:22,749
You never know.

681
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:24,334
You don't think it's enough?

682
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:26,087
- Turn around.
- Okay.

683
00:33:26,587 --> 00:33:28,381
You need some on your back.

684
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:30,632
I'll put some on your back too.

685
00:33:30,633 --> 00:33:32,634
When we get there,

686
00:33:32,635 --> 00:33:35,721
will we clearly see the Cores?

687
00:33:35,722 --> 00:33:36,888
It's the two red areas.

688
00:33:36,889 --> 00:33:38,306
- Two red areas?
- The protrusions.

689
00:33:38,307 --> 00:33:40,600
- Two red ones.
- Who will do the injecting?

690
00:33:40,601 --> 00:33:42,352
Let's decide who will do it.

691
00:33:42,353 --> 00:33:43,395
REACHING OUT

692
00:33:43,396 --> 00:33:44,563
Gabee?

693
00:33:44,564 --> 00:33:45,398
NODS

694
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:48,692
<i>The truth is</i>

695
00:33:48,693 --> 00:33:53,071
I reached out to hold it for her
because it looked heavy.

696
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:54,448
But she asked if I would do it.

697
00:33:54,449 --> 00:33:56,409
So, I just went along with it.

698
00:33:57,201 --> 00:33:59,369
FEELING CONFLICTED

699
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:01,455
- Do-hoon?
- You do it, Do-hoon.

700
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:02,456
Hey, be careful.

701
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:03,832
You'll fall over if you run.

702
00:34:03,833 --> 00:34:05,792
- Be really careful.
- It's really slippery.

703
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:07,794
- Let's do this.
- You have time. We'll open the door.

704
00:34:07,795 --> 00:34:09,087
- All right.
- Let's do this.

705
00:34:09,088 --> 00:34:11,173
CAN WE REALLY DO THIS?

706
00:34:11,174 --> 00:34:13,425
We'll secure the escape routes.

707
00:34:13,426 --> 00:34:15,053
- Where are you going, Gabee?
- We'll do that.

708
00:34:15,678 --> 00:34:16,762
She must be scared.

709
00:34:16,763 --> 00:34:18,138
DRIPPING

710
00:34:18,139 --> 00:34:20,266
Once we get inside,

711
00:34:20,767 --> 00:34:21,683
we have to be silent.

712
00:34:21,684 --> 00:34:23,393
- The mutants have bad vision.
- They can't see.

713
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:24,811
But they are sensitive to sounds.

714
00:34:24,812 --> 00:34:25,896
Hang on.

715
00:34:25,897 --> 00:34:27,773
- Where do we inject this?
- The red parts.

716
00:34:27,774 --> 00:34:29,316
- Into the red Core.
- That's right.

717
00:34:29,317 --> 00:34:31,151
- We need to inject both?
- We'll help you find it.

718
00:34:31,152 --> 00:34:32,903
Don't get nervous.

719
00:34:32,904 --> 00:34:33,987
We don't need to run.

720
00:34:33,988 --> 00:34:35,280
They think we're one of them.

721
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:37,240
- If we run, they'll react to the noise.
- That's true.

722
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:38,408
- You don't need to rush.
- Okay.

723
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:39,494
Stay silent.

724
00:34:53,549 --> 00:34:58,054
WE ARE ONE OF YOU

725
00:35:00,556 --> 00:35:02,517
IS THE MUTANT APPROACHING YONG-JIN?

726
00:35:03,851 --> 00:35:05,728
DISGUISE SUCCESSFUL

727
00:35:09,315 --> 00:35:11,317
CAUTIOUS

728
00:35:12,693 --> 00:35:15,196
GROWL

729
00:35:16,405 --> 00:35:18,491
GROWL

730
00:35:24,580 --> 00:35:27,834
ENTERING CAREFULLY

731
00:35:44,517 --> 00:35:47,436
APPROACHING QUIETLY

732
00:35:52,859 --> 00:35:57,029
RED PROTRUSIONS?

733
00:35:58,531 --> 00:36:00,992
WHERE MIGHT THE CORE BE?

734
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:09,959
I don't think that's it.

735
00:36:11,961 --> 00:36:16,464
STRUGGLING TO FIND THE CORE

736
00:36:16,465 --> 00:36:17,842
What's that?

737
00:36:21,888 --> 00:36:22,846
Is this it?

738
00:36:22,847 --> 00:36:24,015
I DON'T THINK SO

739
00:36:24,599 --> 00:36:25,892
I can't find it.

740
00:36:28,811 --> 00:36:30,812
Even though we had a safety net,

741
00:36:30,813 --> 00:36:34,150
<i>I was worried about what would happen
when they saw through the disguise.</i>

742
00:36:34,692 --> 00:36:36,611
<i>It was really nerve-racking.</i>

743
00:36:37,403 --> 00:36:38,863
There are more outside, right?

744
00:36:39,780 --> 00:36:42,908
THE MUTANTS ARE EVERYWHERE

745
00:36:42,909 --> 00:36:47,538
THE CORE HAS YET TO BE FOUND

746
00:36:49,749 --> 00:36:50,791
It's not this, is it?

747
00:36:52,543 --> 00:36:54,002
MUST INJECT NEEDLES INTO THE CORE

748
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:55,921
CORE IDENTIFIED

749
00:36:55,922 --> 00:36:57,547
When I looked at the bottom,

750
00:36:57,548 --> 00:37:00,759
I found two parts
that looked like blood vessels.

751
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:04,095
THE TWO CORES WERE AT THE BASE

752
00:37:04,096 --> 00:37:06,223
Come down here.

753
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:07,058
They are here.

754
00:37:09,101 --> 00:37:12,271
GABEE AND DO-HOON MOVE TOWARD THE CORE

755
00:37:16,150 --> 00:37:17,944
One, two, three.

756
00:37:18,736 --> 00:37:20,404
INJECTING THE NEEDLES

757
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:22,197
FLUSTERED

758
00:37:22,198 --> 00:37:24,575
Can you help me? It's not going in.

759
00:37:26,827 --> 00:37:28,454
SHAKING

760
00:37:44,762 --> 00:37:45,720
It's done.

761
00:37:45,721 --> 00:37:48,098
AFTER INJECTING THE LIQUIDS

762
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:51,978
THE AGENTS ESCAPE IN CASE OF AN EXPLOSION

763
00:38:07,285 --> 00:38:10,621
THE MUTANTS CHASE AFTER THE AGENTS

764
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:30,807
- Is it over?
- They're dead.

765
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:31,975
Are they dead?

766
00:38:31,976 --> 00:38:35,061
Dozens of mutants were after us as we ran…

767
00:38:35,062 --> 00:38:38,815
But once we destroyed their central node,

768
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:42,236
<i>it was all over.</i>

769
00:38:45,197 --> 00:38:46,490
It's over.

770
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:03,006
- I was so scared.
- Let's go.

771
00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:04,549
That was terrifying.

772
00:39:04,550 --> 00:39:06,384
- Great job.
- That was a tough one.

773
00:39:06,385 --> 00:39:07,469
Thank you.

774
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:10,472
- I couldn't get the needle in.
- It was so stiff.

775
00:39:10,473 --> 00:39:12,390
- Look at that.
- There are more here.

776
00:39:12,391 --> 00:39:14,602
- There are mutants here too.
- They're all over.

777
00:39:16,604 --> 00:39:18,855
- It's so chaotic.
- No doubt.

778
00:39:18,856 --> 00:39:20,982
Yong-jin, it's here.

779
00:39:20,983 --> 00:39:23,110
- The mutant broke through this window.
- Yes.

780
00:39:23,903 --> 00:39:25,236
- No way.
- Oh, that's here?

781
00:39:25,237 --> 00:39:27,947
What was Illon H. Na up to?

782
00:39:27,948 --> 00:39:29,949
- Why did he have all this?
- Right?

783
00:39:29,950 --> 00:39:33,661
The materials are the data we gave out.

784
00:39:33,662 --> 00:39:36,998
Now that I think about it,

785
00:39:36,999 --> 00:39:39,794
we were the ones
who leaked the classified information.

786
00:39:40,503 --> 00:39:42,462
Does XIN know we did it?

787
00:39:42,463 --> 00:39:45,048
We solved the issue
of being tricked last time.

788
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:46,091
- That's right.
- In that case,

789
00:39:46,092 --> 00:39:48,218
now that we've saved the earth…

790
00:39:48,219 --> 00:39:50,345
- Let's have a beer.
- Sounds good.

791
00:39:50,346 --> 00:39:55,225
I'm sure the viewers at home
are living very peacefully.

792
00:39:55,226 --> 00:39:58,436
That's because we succeeded today.

793
00:39:58,437 --> 00:40:01,564
You're able to live peacefully
because of us.

794
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:04,192
Let's go back to the headquarters
and have a beer.

795
00:40:04,193 --> 00:40:05,276
The headquarters was destroyed.

796
00:40:05,277 --> 00:40:06,528
Should we go to Seoul, then?

797
00:40:06,529 --> 00:40:07,445
Let's go.

798
00:40:07,446 --> 00:40:09,697
Let's go, XIN Seoul Division!

799
00:40:09,698 --> 00:40:11,492
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

800
